### SIGNAL GENERATION PATTERNS:

```python
# Pattern 1: Vectorized boolean conditions (PREFERRED — fast)
close = df["close"].values
long_cond = (rsi_val < 30) & (close < lower)
short_cond = (rsi_val > 70) & (close > upper)
signals = pd.Series(0.0, index=df.index, dtype=np.float64)
signals[long_cond] = 1.0
signals[short_cond] = -1.0

# Pattern 2: Crossover detection (for MACD, EMA, etc.)
cross_up = (macd_line[1:] > signal_line[1:]) & (macd_line[:-1] <= signal_line[:-1])
cross_down = (macd_line[1:] < signal_line[1:]) & (macd_line[:-1] >= signal_line[:-1])
signals.iloc[1:][cross_up] = 1.0
signals.iloc[1:][cross_down] = -1.0

# Pattern 3: Skip warmup period (avoids NaN-driven false signals)
warmup = params.get("warmup", 50)
signals.iloc[:warmup] = 0.0
```

### STOP-LOSS / TAKE-PROFIT:
The engine automatically applies SL/TP if these params are present in default_params:
- `stop_atr_mult`: stop-loss distance = stop_atr_mult * ATR (e.g. 1.5)
- `tp_atr_mult`: take-profit distance = tp_atr_mult * ATR (e.g. 3.0)

You do NOT need to implement SL/TP logic in generate_signals.
Just include `"atr"` in required_indicators and these params in default_params.

